24
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,240
 I go.

25
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,320
 You do."

26
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:14,920
 Because silence leads to faith, and faith then always leads forth into action.

27
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:17,960
 Tonight, we're starting a brand new series, which is going to be a very short series.

28
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:21,160
 It's only three weeks long, but this is the heart of it.

29
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:26,560
 We want to talk to you about what real, genuine belief actually is.

30
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:31,400
 Not just the faith that saves, but the faith that moves, that actually leads you out of

31
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:35,800
 this room and into the world and changes the way in which you engage it therefrom.

32
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,800
 That's what we want to do.

33
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:42,460
 And the reason why we're doing it is because just a couple of months back, in the middle

34
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:47,260
 of the night, February 25th specifically, I woke up suddenly.

35
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:50,280
 My heart was racing.

36
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:56,040
 Not just a little fast, but I mean it was pounding in my chest to the point that I woke

37
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:58,360
 up and I was worried.

38
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:01,760
 I was thinking, "God, is this what a heart attack feels like?

39
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,520
 I know I'm getting older, but I'm still young, man.

40
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,880
 I'm not ready to go yet."

41
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:11,640
 And so as I laid there in bed, flat on my back, eyes wide open, feeling myself totally

